==English==

===Noun===
'''Sinhala'''

# (also referred to as Sinhalese; earlier referred to as Singhalese) is the mother tongue of the Sinhalese,Homo Sapiens first appeared in Sri Lanka about 500,000 B.C. Few artifacts have been found dating back to subsequent Paleolithic culture of the second Stone age period. Stone cultures endured until about 1000 B.C. The second phase of stone age may have ended some few centuries later with the establishment of metal. The Stone working culture was known as Balandoga Culture. They first made an impression on island life about 5000 B.C and spread through out the Sri Lanka.The Balangoda Manawaya survived until about 500 B.C and true history faded out under the advance of early settlers from India.People who protect load buddha s word
. The term Sinhala is derived from the Sinhalese term සිංහල (siṃhala, pronounced /ˈsiŋhələ/).


